import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=30, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of delay time?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Delay Time")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    average_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='origin_destination', y='distance', data=data, ci=None)
    ax.axhline(average_distance, ls='--', color='red', label=f'Average Distance: {average_distance:.2f}')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='origin', columns='destination', values='origin_destination_count', aggfunc='sum')
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(data_pivot, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.0f')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of delay time by origin?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Origin")
    plt.ylabel("Delay")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Origin", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='distance', y='delay', hue='origin_destination', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance traveled?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.legend(title='Origin-Destination', loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.25, 1))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
